CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 8, 1951, pg. 25 reads: "Learning By Doing-High school students lean [sic] modern business methods through extra-curricular activities of Junior Achievement, Inc. Upper left: Photo-Mart members are shown at work making squeeges of this year's high school graduates.  Charles H. Leibson, adviser, inspects work of Joan Stale and Lille Winchester...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Charles H. Leibson, inspects work of Joan Stale and Lille Winchester, working in darkroom during Junior Achievement activity
